                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3702: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-29T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 29, 1932—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 29—11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Paragraph 3 of my January 29, 4 p.m. After communicating Japanese Admiral’s
                    message to the Mayor at 6:30 this afternoon at the Japanese Consul[ate] General
                    an armistice was arranged to become effective at 8 o’clock tonight. We await
                    developments.</p>
                <p>Repeated to [Legation?].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
